quotes.content: That which does not kill us makes us stronger.
quotes.author: Friedrich Nietzsche

quotes.content: Remember no one can make you feel inferior without your consent.
quotes.author: Eleanor Roosevelt

quotes.content: Your worth consists in what you are and not in what you have.
quotes.author: Thomas Edison

quotes.content: Be yourself; everyone else is already taken.
quotes.author: Oscar Wilde

quotes.content: This above all: to thine own self be true.
quotes.author: William Shakespeare

quotes.content: Be who you are and say what you feel, because those who mind don’t matter and those who matter don’t mind.
quotes.author: Bernard M. Baruch

quotes.content: Two roads diverged in a wood, and I—I took the one less traveled by, And that has made all the difference.
quotes.author: Robert Frost
